                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3533.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Chihuahua</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-07T22:00:00-07:04">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 7, 1912—10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> (Received, via El Paso, Tex., April 8, 1912—8.45 p.m.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reported Haberiline,<note n="1" xml:id="d1032fn1">Spelled Heberlein in later
                        telegrams.</note> American, arrested for attempting leave Jimenez contrary
                    orders rebel commander last Friday. Still incarcerated incommunicado. Contrary
                    statement newspapers; no appeal received from prisoner this office and,
                    inferring refusal permission on the part of rebels, I wrote Orozco to-day
                    urgently requesting immediate statement, but communication apparently ignored.
                    Rebels all sullen because of accepted belief partiality of United States for
                    established Government.</p>
                <p>Rebel chiefs issued manifesto yesterday repudiating Vásquez Gómez entirely.</p>
                <p>Orozco has taken no action repudiating Gonzalo Enrile’s letter abusive of the
                    United States, addressed to the President, reprinted and circulated here. But he
                    repudiates the likewise abusive manifesto circulated at the same time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
